==English==

===Etymology===
From Ancient Greek '''[[κάθεξις]]''' ''(kathexis,''  [[holding]], [[retention]]). Entered English language as a translation for the common everyday German word ''besetzung'', which means "occupied". In English translations, a Greek word was used to be more scientific.

===Noun===
Freud used the term to describe the tying up of [[libido]] or mental energy on given [[locus]].

